\f0\fs24 \cf0 The purpose of this course is to introduce (or re-introduce) students to games in multiple types of media, and to the video game industry. During the course, students will learn what makes a game a game while they try their hand at creating a game of their own. They will begin by creating a pitch that encapsulates their game idea in a document. They'll then use that document as a guide while they create their own 3D video game.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298

\b\fs36 \cf0 Goals\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280

\fs28 \cf0 By the end of the course, students will be able to:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs24 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}Explain what a game is\
{\listtext	\'95	}Evaluate a game's strengths and weaknesses\
{\listtext	\'95	}Describe the advantages and disadvantages of different types of game media (board, card, athletic, computer, etc.)\
{\listtext	\'95	}Describe the platform and genre that fit a given game\
{\listtext	\'95	}Differentiate between common game genres\
{\listtext	\'95	}Describe several of the professions that are involved in creating a video game\
{\listtext	\'95	}Create a complete pitch for a new game of the student's own design\
{\listtext	\'95	}Create a vertical slice (small, complete section) of a playable 3D video game that includes the following prefabricated or original assets:\
